		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Saint Paul</placeName> <date>December 8&#44; 5623</date></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Revd. Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">Your worthy and kind letter<lb/> for which I am very greatly <sic>oblige</sic> to you&#44; was handed<lb/> to me by our worthy and most respected <persName>Mr. Cardozo</persName>&#44;<lb/> As the same does&#44; and will do for you&#44; whatever will be<lb/> in his might&#44; and as his influence is very great&#44; I am sure<lb/> your books will be sold here&#44; of course he wrote to you.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">About my letter to <persName>Vice</persName>&#44; certainly I leave every thing<lb/> to you&#44; to act freely&#44; according to your judgment.  But believe<lb/> me sir&#59; that my intention is not to give satisfaction&#44; or to<lb/> justify myself before the world&#44; since I know it <sic>to</sic> well that&#44;<lb/> there are only&#44; who wish to believe wrongly&#44; and do not care<lb/> for the truth&#44; with a very few exception.  My only desire is&#44; to<lb/> convince the so surnamed <persName>Wise</persName> &#40;yet a fool&#41; that he cannot<lb/> injure me&#44; and I am not afraid of him.  The God whom I<lb/> serve&#44; the holy One of <placeName>Israel</placeName>&#44; who <sic>deliverd</sic> me from the<lb/> mouths of lions and tigers&#44; will protect and preserve me<lb/> from the violent&#44; crazy&#44; and mad dog&#45;tar <persName>Vice</persName>&#44; also.<lb/>  And another thing&#44; to let him know that I thank God<lb/> read every day&#44; <add>Hebrew</add>&#44; consequently I know the time<lb/> when I may read it&#44; which it is according to some&#44; <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> <add>Hebrew</add>&#44; that there should be so much day light<lb/> that he may know the difference between a wolf and a dog.<lb/>  Enough sir&#44; I spoke <sic>to</sic> much&#44; and troubled you <sic>to</sic> much<lb/> about such an unworthy low mean fellow&#44; I hope<lb/> you will for give me.</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
			<p rend="indent(1)">About my circumstances&#44; as I know you to be an<lb/> unchangeable and immutable man&#44; and you are<lb/> a friend indeed&#44; <sic>And</sic> <add>Hebrew</add>&#44; though I have my<lb/> failures more than enough&#44; as there is none who fails not.<lb/>  <add>Hebrew</add>&#44; Yet you always wish and desire my<lb/> welfare&#44; I will let you know briefly&#44; <sic>That</sic> during my<lb/> long and great sickness&#44; I lost not only the little<lb/> money I made while at <placeName>Nashville</placeName>&#44; and <placeName>Memphis</placeName>&#44; but<lb/> even my clothing and every thing I had&#44; I came here<lb/> to tell <hi rend="underline">you</hi>&#44; naked and barefooted.  But the all mercy&#45;<lb/>ful heavenly father has sent his good angel before<lb/> me&#44; that is the good kind and honourable <persName>Mr. Cardozo<add>&#63;</add></persName><lb/> He not only takes care that I shall have every thing<lb/> needful for myself&#44; but I am able to send to <sic>send</sic> to<lb/> my family something every month.  He also takes<lb/> care&#44; and tries to make a man of me&#44; which I have<lb/> not been till now&#44; which brought me to all mis&#45;<lb/>fortune I hope that I will prove to be a good disciple<lb/> and that he may be glad&#44; that he led me&#44; and trained me<lb/> up in the path I shall go.  His lady though has servants<lb/> attends every thing in house&#44; not trusting to a none Israelite<lb/> They are kind hearted and good and pious Israelites.  I<lb/> hope&#44; if not <sic>to</sic> much trouble&#44; as I know your time<lb/> is very much occupied and engaged&#44; to be honoured with<lb/> your answer.  Till then I remain</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">Dear and Revd. Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">your most faithful and obedient servant</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">E. Marcuson</persName></p>
				<p>Please sir send me a NS</p>
				<p>if possible.</p>
		</body>
